#!hexa strict
// stdlib/booksim/traffic.hexa — synthetic-traffic generators (CLEAN-ROOM)
//
// @version 0.0.1-skeleton
// @capabilities [traffic, permutation, random]
// @stability skeleton (no bodies — TBD; pending rfc_001 §8 GREEN)
// @since 2026-05-18
//
// CLEAN-ROOM PROVENANCE (design.md Decision 1)
//   Re-derives the public surface of BookSim2's TrafficPattern hierarchy:
//   - upstream code   : src/traffic.cpp:48-194  (TrafficPattern::New dispatch),
//                       :230-250 (TransposeTrafficPattern::dest),
//                       :289-308 (TornadoTrafficPattern::dest),
//                       :380-396 (UniformRandomTrafficPattern::dest)
//   - upstream spec   : doc/manual.tex §traffic_patterns
//   - upstream license: BSD-2-Clause (Stanford 2007-2015)
//   - upstream commit : 28f43299f1706a3160ffac721ca461d74eb6e618
//   - external theorem: Dally & Towles, PPIN §3 (traffic-pattern taxonomy);
//                       tornado is the canonical adversarial-bisection
//                       stressor (rfc_001 §3, §9).
//   No code copied from upstream.
//
// Source: rfc_001 §3 minimal subset.

use "stdlib/qrng/router"   // for uniform's per-call random choice

// ─── public types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// The three traffic kinds in rfc_001 §3 minimal subset.
// CLEAN-ROOM (traffic.cpp:48-194 TrafficPattern::New string dispatch).
enum TrafficKind {
    UNIFORM,        // uniform random — traffic.cpp:380-396
    TRANSPOSE,      // bit-transpose permutation — traffic.cpp:230-250
    TORNADO,        // adversarial-bisection rotate-by-((k+1)/2-1) — traffic.cpp:289-308
}

// Single traffic specification — pure data, no state.
// k, n, xr mirror BookSim2's per-traffic-pattern arguments per
// doc/manual.tex §traffic_patterns table.
struct TrafficSpec {
    kind:  TrafficKind,
    k:     int,         // radix per dimension (e.g. 8 for an 8x8 mesh)
    n:     int,         // dimension count   (e.g. 2 for a 2-D mesh)
    xr:    int,         // concentration     (1 unless cmesh; rfc_001 chip scope = 1)
    seed:  int,         // RNG seed for uniform's per-call choice (deterministic reproduction)
}

// ─── per-kind destination functions ─────────────────────────────────────

